        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali38-kilavi">iḵtu iravukkuṟi vantu nīṅkun talaivaṉai etirppaṭṭut tōḻi 
            talaiviyatu nilaimai kūṟi avaṉai varaivu kaṭāva, avaṉ varaiyavarukiṉṟamai tōḻi talaivikku 
            varaivumalintu kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante, meeting the hero who left after having come to the night tryst, told the heroine, rejoicing at the marriage, the confidante of the coming(?) when she had urged him for marriage talking about the heroine's state [and] he [willing to] marry.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali38">
                <l>imaiyavil vāṅkiya vīrñcaṭai yantaṇa</l>
                <l>ṉumaiyamarn tuyarmalai yiruntaṉa ṉāka</l>
                <l>vaiyiru talaiyi ṉarakkar kōmāṉ</l>
                <l>ṟoṭipoli taṭakkaiyiṟ kīḻpukut tammalai</l>
                <l>yeṭukkal cellā tuḻappavaṉ pōla</l>
                <l>vuṟupuli yuruvēyppap pūtta vēṅkaiyaik</l>
                <l>kaṟuvukoṇ ṭataṉmutaṟ kuttiya matayāṉai</l>
                <l>nīṭiru viṭarakañ cilampak kūuyttaṉ</l>
                <l>kōṭupuyk kallā tuḻakku nāṭakēḷ;</l>
                <l rend="space">āriṭai yeṉṉāynī yaravañcāy vantakkā</l>
                <l>ṉīraṟṟa pulamēpōṟ pulleṉṟāḷ vaikaṟai</l>
                <l>kārpeṟṟa pulamēpōṟ kaviṉpeṟu makkaviṉ</l>
                <l>ṟīrāmaṟ kāppatōr tiṟaṉuṇṭē luraittaikkāṇ;</l>
                <l rend="space">iruḷiṭai yeṉṉāynī yiravañcāy vantakkāṟ</l>
                <l>poruḷillā ṉiḷamaipōṟ pulleṉṟāḷ vaikaṟai</l>
                <l>yaruḷvallā ṉākkampō laṇipeṟu mavvaṇi</l>
                <l>teruḷāmaṟ kāppatōr tiṟaṉuṇṭē luraittaikkāṇ;</l>
                <l rend="space">maṟantiruntā reṉṉāynī malaiyiṭai vantakkā</l>
                <l>laṟañcārāṉ mūppēpō laḻitakkāḷ vaikaṟai</l>
                <l>tiṟañcērntā ṉākkampōṟ ṟiruttaku mattirup</l>
                <l>puṟaṅkūṟṟut tīrppatōr poruḷuṇṭē luraittaikkāṇ;</l>
                <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku,</l>
                <l>niṉṉuṟu viḻumaṅ kūṟak kēṭṭu</l>
                <l>varumē tōḻi naṉmalai nāṭaṉ</l>
                <l>vēṅkai viriviṭa nōkki</l>
                <l>vīṅkiṟaip paṇaittōḷ varaintaṉaṉ koḷaṟkē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="9">Listen, man from the land, where suffers, without extracting its tusk, </l>
<l>the rutting elephant, who took exception to the kino tree that flowered</l>
<l corresp="6f">so as to resemble the form of the tiger it had fought, [and] pierced it, </l>
<l corresp="8">trumpeting so that it resounded inside long dark caves, </l>
<l corresp="5d">like </l>
<l corresp="3">the king of the Rakṣasas with five [times] two heads </l>
<l>who, while the brahmin with wet matted hair who drew the bow on the Himālaya,</l>
<l corresp="1f">was on the high mountain, resting with Umā,</l>
<l corresp="4a-c">entered below with [his] broad hands flourishing with bracelets </l>
<l corresp="4df">[and] suffered, not being able to lift that mountain, </l>
<l rend="space">You who don’t say the way is difficult, you who do not fear snakes, at the time [you] came [back]</l>
<l>she would be empty just like the field where the water ceased. She obtains beauty</l>
<l>just like the field that obtained the monsoon rains at dawn. If it is a means</l>
<l>that preserves that beauty from ending, see what [I] have told [you].</l>
<l rend="space">You who don’t speak of [being] ainmidst the darkness, you who don’t fear night, at the time [you] came [back]</l>
<l>she would be empty just like the youth of one without wealth. She obtains adornment</l>
<l>like the gain of one strong in consideration at dawn. If it is a means</l>
<l>that preserves those adornments from being clear(???), see what [I] have told [you].</l>
<l rend="space">You who do not speak of this imperfect in bravery, at the time you came [back] from the mountains</l>
<l>she would be fit to perish just like the old age of one who was not full of Dharma. She is fit for brilliance</l>
<l>like the gain of one who joined ??? at dawn. If it is wealth </l>
<l>that slanders [and] ends that brilliance, see what [I] have told [you].</l>
<l rend="space">That is to say,</l>
<l rend="space">when he listens when [I] talked about the distress you have</l>
<l>he will come [back], friend, the man from the land of good mountains,</l>
<l>looking at the place of the flowering of the kino tree,</l>
<l>in order to take [your] bamboo shoulders with bulging joint as one who has married [you].</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
